(16, 'The Powerful IKN! Kalimantan Timur Segera Hadir Konstruksi Pembangunan Pertamina Sustainable Energy,', 'HARIANHALUAN.COM - Pembangunan konstruksi mega proyek di Kalimantan Timur mengenai proyek Pertamina Sustainable Energy Center IKN.\n\nOtorita Ibu Kota Nusantara dan Pertamina tandatangani nota kesepahaman (MoU) untuk pembangunan Pertamina Sustainable Energy Center (Pusat Energi Berkelanjutan).\n\nKerja Sama ini yang merupakan salah satu bentuk dukungan Pertamina untuk wujudkan target Net Zero Emission pada tahun 2045.\n\nProyek ini masuk dalam tahap 3 groundbreaking yang telah dilakukan dan diadakan pada 20-21 Desember 2023, dengan fokus pada sektor ruang hijau. \n\n\"Peran Pertamina di kawasan riset & inovasi ini diharapkan berkontribusi dalam membangun masa depan Ibu Kota Nusantara sebagai smart sustainable forest city,”\n\n“Sebagai BUMN pertama yang menandatangani MOU dengan OIKN, Pertamina diharapkan turut menjadi,” \n\n“penggerak investasi di Ibu Kota Nusantara,\" ucap Kepala OIKN, Bambang Susantono.\n\nRencananya Pusat Energi Berkelanjutan yang akan dibangun di Wilayah Perencanaan 5 IKN, dengan luas sekitar 3.720 hektare. \n\nProses pembangunan yang akan dilakukan secara bertahap dengan dilanjutkan sejumlah fasilitas meliputi Pertamina Sustainability Academy.\n\nPertamina Training Insititute, Pertamina Research and Innovation Center for Sustainable and Low Carbon Technologies. \n\nSelain itu, Pertamina Vocational Education Center, Shared Green Infrastructure, Laboratorium, dan Sustainability Start-up Hub.\n\nMenurut Nicke, IKN memiliki potensi untuk tidak hanya mencapai Net Zero Emission tetapi hingga menjadi negative emission. \n\n\"Di IKN ini punya kawasan hutan yang cukup luas. Ini bisa menjadi natural based solutions semacam carbon sink,”\n\n“yang bisa menyerap atau menyimpan secara alami emisi itu sendiri,\" tutur Nicke sebagaimana dikutip HarianHaluan.com dari ikn.go.id.\n\nSebagai tahap awal Pertamina akan mulai dengan membangun Pusat Energi Berkelanjutan. \n\nKemudian, Pertamina juga akan mempersiapkan sumber daya manusianya melalui program vokasi.***\n\n', 'uploads/image-4-1579078626 (1).png', '2024-05-05 11:07:52', 1, 'rejected', 'TES REJECT APAKAH BERHASIL', NULL),
(47, 'Each year the stakes grow higher in the fight to save the environment and combat global warming. Now', 'Each year the stakes grow higher in the fight to save the environment and combat global warming. Now more than ever, we’re aware of the damaging effects that our current dependence on fossil fuels holds for our collective futures. One of the key solutions? Sustainable energy.\n\nFossil fuels (e.g. coal, natural gas and oil) are not only harmful to the planet when burned daily for energy, but they’re also unsustainable as finite resources. Sustainability refers to the concept that all people can meet their basic needs infinitely, without compromising future generations. Sustainability in terms of energy embraces the same principles.\n\nOne day the world will run out of fossil fuels. Read on to discover how sustainable energy matters and its significance when it comes to the future of our planet.\n\nWhat is sustainable energy?\nSustainable energy includes any energy source that cannot be depleted and can remain viable forever. It does not need to be renewed or replenished; sustainable energy meets our demand for energy without any risk of going bad or running out. This is why sustainable energy is the answer to our energy needs.\n\nFurthermore, sustainable energy doesn’t harm the environment (or at most, there is a minimal risk), increase climate change or cost a heavy price. Although there is a cost associated with creating and building ways to capture sustainable energy, the energy sources themselves are typically free.\n\nExamples of sustainable energy sources include wind, solar and water (hydropower). All of which can be considered inexhaustible and widely available to almost everyone. Geothermal energy can also be included as a sustainable alternative energy source. Geothermal energy creates usable energy from the planet’s internal energy sources, such as geysers.\n\nSustainable energy systems are dependent upon engineers to further progress. For an in-depth introduction to sustainable energy, explore Toolseeram Ramjeawon’s “Introduction to Sustainability for Engineers.” This book provides students with a framework for how to put sustainability into practice. It also highlights the design process and offers a variety of case studies to comprehensively cover sustainable energy.\n\nWhat is the difference between sustainable and renewable energy?\nPeople often use the terms “sustainable” and “renewable” interchangeably. However, there is a difference between the two: the possibility of replenishment.\n\nSustainable energy, as highlighted above, is theoretically inexhaustible. It cannot be depleted because sustainable energy sources don’t need to be replenished. For example, think of the sun or wind. Neither resource needs to be created or replaced.\n\nOn the other hand, renewable energy is theoretically exhaustible — it uses resources from the earth that can naturally be replenished, such as crops and biomatter. A renewable energy source like bioenergy uses biological masses (e.g. agricultural byproducts like straw and manure) to create energy. Another example of bioenergy is ethanol, which is made from sugarcane and corn. Since these crops can be planted and farmed to generate more energy, it’s a type of renewable energy. For more information on renewable energy systems, take a look at Vladimir Strezov and Hossain Md. Anawar’s “Renewable Energy Systems from Biomass: Efficiency, Innovation and Sustainability,” which explores the ties between bio-related renewable energy systems and overall sustainability:\n\nImage showing energy crisis with fossil fuels becoming scarce and rising CO2 emissions. New renewable energy sources depicted.\n\nAnother helpful resource is Ram K. Gupta and Tuan Anh Nguyen’s “Energy from Waste: Production and Storage,” which considers how waste from various sources can be used in energy production and storage applications. It similarly discusses the connections between renewable energy systems and long-term sustainability.\n\nDifferent types of renewable energy are just as important in the search for clean energy options because they don’t pollute the atmosphere, increase climate change or cause more damage to the environment.\n\nWhat are the benefits of sustainable energy?\nThere is a broad range of benefits to transitioning to sustainable energy. Below we’ll list the top ways sustainable energy can positively impact our communities and planet:\n\nIcon image of a heart beat line leading to a heart - to represent health and the importance of healthImproves Public Health\nThe burning of fossil fuels in coal and natural gas plants is directly tied with many serious public health issues, such as neurological damage, cancer, heart attacks, breathing problems and premature death. When fossil fuels are burned for energy, they release air and water pollution that negatively affect surrounding communities and environments.\n\nHowever, all of these associated risks can be eliminated by switching to sustainable energy. Sustainable energy sources typically emit no air or water pollutants that can harm public health. They also don’t make a negative impact or strain on local water resources. Meanwhile, coal mining, natural gas drilling and thermal power plants all compete with local agriculture, drinking water and other important community water needs for resources.\n\nIcon image of a person running up an arrow with a briefcase - to represent work and sit by the copy about creating local jobsCreates Local Jobs \nSustainable energy can also help fuel your local communities. Since most facilities and sustainable energy infrastructure must be built locally or in the same county, making the switch helps create jobs and improve the economy. Instead of spending more money importing energy from fossil fuel companies, that money is spent on materials and workmanship to maintain sustainable energy facilities.\n \n\nIcon image of a foot with CO2 written on it - to represent carbon footprint and sit by the copy about decreasing your carbon footprintDecreases Your Carbon Footprint \nWe’re all doing our best to reduce our negative impact on the environment, but there is only so much each person can do. Sustainable energy, such as wind and solar energy, creates zero carbon emissions that can harm the atmosphere and contribute to global warming. It offsets the need for fossil fuels, which are actively increasing climate change and polluting our earth.\n\nSimply switching your own home’s energy source can help cut the environmental impact you and your family have on the planet — and eliminate your dependence on fossil fuels.\n\nIcon image of an energy coin falling into a piggy bank - to represent energy cost and sit by the copy about the long term cost of sustainable energy being more affordable Long-term Cost is More Affordable \nSustainable energy can make a huge long-term difference to the electricity and energy costs of our homes and businesses — no matter where you are. Not only are they easily available for little to no cost, but they’re much more cost-effective than traditional energy resources, such as power plants.\n\n\nMaking the financial leap to wind, solar or any other sustainable energy source may seem daunting at first because of installation costs, but the long-term investment pays off in just a few years. In fact, sustainable energy costs decrease each and every year. Depending on your country or state, you may even get tax reductions for choosing sustainable energy. Ultimately, you could end up saving exponentially just by making the switch to a sustainable energy system like solar panels.\n\nIcon image of a padlock with an energy symbol on it - to represent energy security and sit by the copy about sustainable energy being the most reliable form of energy, thus providing security \n\nEnergy Security \nSustainable energy is by definition the most reliable form of energy. It will never deplete and can remove our reliance on imported fossil fuels, which are growing more expensive and less accessible. Sustainable energy also helps to conserve the planet’s natural resources and reduce the pollution associated with unsustainable energy.\n\nWhy is sustainable energy important for our future?\nWhen we consider sustainable energy and our future, it’s essential to also understand what the current energy crisis is doing to our planet right now.\n\nDue to human activity, the earth has grown 1.5 degrees hotter since the industrial revolution — a staggering amount in such a short period of time compared to pre-industrial revolution times. Many factors have contributed to this increase, but a major cause is our burning of fossil fuels for energy. The most prevalent greenhouse gas is carbon dioxide (CO2), which has triggered immense global warming.\n\nAlthough carbon is an essential element within the earth’s ecosystem, there needs to be a sustainable balance — which is not the current situation. Carbon particles have become trapped in the earth’s atmosphere, between the surface and ozone layer. This is insulating our planet and warming it up, which is causing catastrophic effects: glaciers are melting, sea levels are rising and extreme weather events (e.g. hurricanes, heatwaves and floods) are escalating.\n\nBeyond that, finite energy source facilities are polluting the air, water and soil increasingly every day. Besides destroying our natural environments, it’s causing undue harm to the health of people globally.\n\nAlthough humans have done irreversible damage to the environment, there’s still hope in how we maintain and mitigate repercussions for future generations. The solution lies in how we stop flooding our atmosphere with carbon dioxide and reduce our emissions.\n\nRemember, sustainable energy produces little to no global warming emissions. By choosing sustainable energy resources and committing to clean energy, humans can effectively slow down the acceleration of climate change.\n\nTo learn more about the chemistry behind sustainable energy, we have two books that can help you get started. Nancy E. Carpenter’s “Chemistry of Sustainable Energy” is a great resource for students who want to understand the fundamental principles of chemistry that tie into long-term energy solutions, including wind power, fuel cells, solar photovoltaics, biomass conversion processes and next-generation nuclear power.\n\nFor a university-level environmental chemistry approach integrated with toxicological chemistry, there is Stanley E. Manahan’s “Fundamentals of Environmental and Toxicological Chemistry: Sustainable Science.” This best-seller focuses on the relationship between sustainability and green chemistry, and how they impact the five environmental spheres (hydrosphere, atmosphere, geosphere, biosphere and anthroposphere).\n\n', 'uploads/taking-beautiful-photos-of-nature-2.png', '2024-05-07 10:57:59', 1, 'approved', '', NULL),
(58, 'Energi Hijau Masa Depan! Membongkar Mitos & Fakta Energi Terbarukan!!!', 'Pernah kah kalian dengar tentang energi terbarukan? Kalo belum, yuk simak blog ini!\n\nDi era modern ini, bumi kita mulai ngos-ngosan nih. Polusi makin parah, perubahan iklim makin ngeri. Salah satu solusinya? Beralih ke energi hijau alias energi terbarukan!\n\nTapi kenapa ya, banyak banget mitos yang beredar tentang energi terbarukan. Katanya sih mahal, gak efisien, gak bisa ngecover kebutuhan energi, ribet, dan lain sebagainya. Bener gak sih?\n\nYuk, kita bongkar mitos-mitos itu bareng-bareng!\n\nMitos ke-1: Energi Terbarukan Mahal dan Gak Efisien!\n\nFaktanya: Dulu sih emang iya, teknologinya masih mahal. Tapi sekarang udah jauh lebih murah! Efisiensi energi terbarukan juga terus meningkat, contohnya tenaga surya dan angin yang sekarang udah bisa menghasilkan energi yang cukup besar.\n\nMitos ke-2: Gak Bisa Penuhi Kebutuhan Energi Global\n\nFaktanya: Potensi energi terbarukan di bumi tuh gede banget, jauh lebih besar dari kebutuhan energi global. Contohnya, energi matahari yang mencapai bumi dalam satu jam aja cukup buat memenuhi kebutuhan energi seluruh dunia selama setahun!\n\nMitos ke-3: Energi Terbarukan tuh Cuman Cocok Buat Negara Maju\n\nFaktanya: Salah banget! Negara berkembang kayak Indonesia tuh punya potensi besar banget buat manfaatin energi terbarukan. Iklim tropis yang cerah dan sumber daya alam yang melimpah bikin Indonesia cocok banget buat ngembangin energi surya, panas bumi, dan energi angin.\n\nMitos ke- 4: Energi Terbarukan itu Gak Stabil dan Gak Bisa Diandalkan\n\nFaktanya: Teknologi penyimpanan energi kayak baterai terus berkembang pesat, jadi energi terbarukan bisa disimpan dan dipake pas dibutuhkan. Kombinasi berbagai sumber energi terbarukan juga bisa bantu atasi intermittency dan memastikan pasokan energi yang stabil.\n\nMitos ke-5: Gak Ramah Lingkungan\n\nFaktanya: Energi terbarukan kayak tenaga surya, angin, dan air gak menghasilkan emisi gas rumah kaca yang bikin perubahan iklim. Gak cuma itu, energi terbarukan juga gak menghasilkan limbah berbahaya kayak energi fosil.\n\nJadi Kesimpulan nya adalah: \nEnergi terbarukan bukan cuma solusi masa depan, tapi juga solusi masa kini!  Teknologi terus berkembang, biayanya makin murah, dan kesadaran akan kelestarian lingkungan makin tinggi. Yuk, kita sama-sama beralih ke energi hijau dan ciptakan masa depan yang lebih cerah dan berkelanjutan!', 'uploads/WhatsApp Image 2024-05-08 at 00.26.28.jpeg', '2024-05-07 16:26:48', 1, 'approved', '', NULL),
(59, ' Angin Bisa Jadi Listrik? Ini Cara Kerja Energi Terbarukan yang Unik!!!', 'Kalian pernah ngelihat kincir angin raksasa yang muter-muter di bukit atau pantai? Kincir angin itu bukan cuma pemanis pemandangan, gengs!  Mereka jagoan yang bisa menghasilkan listrik, keren kan?  Mungkin kamu mikir, \"Hah, angin kok bisa jadi listrik?\"  Tenang, sekarang kita bongkar rahasia di balik energi terbarukan yang unik ini!\n\n1. Angin Kencang, Baling-baling Ikutan Kencang!\n\nPertama, kincir angin punya baling-baling gede yang dirancang khusus. Baling-baling ini kayak sayap pesawat terbang yang didesain buat ngeluarin performa maksimal pas ngelawan angin.  Semakin kenceng anginnya, semakin cepet putaran baling-balingnya.  Bayangin kayak kamu lagi main layangan, layangannya bakal terbang tinggi kalau anginnya kenceng, kan?\n\n2. Poros Baling-baling Terhubung ke Generator\n\nPoros yang nempel di tengah baling-baling ini nyambung ke generator. Nah, generator ini alat canggih yang bisa ngubah energi gerak putaran baling-baling jadi energi mekanik. Gimana kalo kamu bayangin kamu lagi ngegowes sepeda statis?  Energi gerak kamu itu diubah jadi energi mekanik yang bisa membuat roda berputar, kan?  Nah, prinsipnya mirip kayak gitu!\n\n3. Energi Mekanik Jadi Listrik!\n\nGenerator nggak berhenti cuma di energi mekanik aja. Generator ini punya kumparan magnet yang bisa ngubah energi mekanik tadi jadi energi listrik. Prosesnya agak rumit, tapi bayangin kayak kamu ngesetin tali dynamo di sepeda kamu.  Gesekan tali itu sama magnet di dynamo bakal ngubah energi gerak kamu jadi energi listrik buat ngasih lampu sepeda kamu nyala.  Keren, kan?\n\n4. Energi Listrik Dialirkan ke Jaringan Listrik!\n\nListrik yang dihasilkan generator ini nggak cuma dipakai kincir angin doang.  Listrik dialirin ke gardu listrik lewat kabel bawah tanah atau kabel udara.  Dari gardu listrik, baru deh listrik didistribusikan ke rumah, sekolah, pabrik, dan tempat-tempat lain.  Jadi, nggak cuma kincir angin aja yang ngerasain manfaat angin kenceng, tapi juga hp kamu di rumah!\n\nKenapa Energi Angin itu Keren Abis????\n\n* Ramah Lingkungan: Tidak seperti ngebakar bensin yang ngeluarin gas rumah kaca dan bikin polusi udara, energi angin bebas emisi!  Bumi jadi sehat dan nggak gampang panas.\n* Sumber Tak Terbatas: Angin tuh kayak temen yang selalu ada, bisa diandalin.  Kita nggak perlu takut kehabisan angin kayak kita takut kehabisan bensin. \n* Hemat Budget: Lama-lama, energi angin lebih murah dibanding listrik biasa.  Bayangin, kamu nggak perlu beli bensin lagi buat ngasih listrik ke rumah kamu!\n* Fleksibel Banget: Kincir angin bisa dipasang di darat atau di laut, bebas deh!  Asal ada angin kenceng, energi bisa dihasilkan.\n\nYuk, Dukung Energi Terbarukan!\n\nDengan pake energi terbarukan kayak angin, kita bisa bikin masa depan yang lebih sehat, keren, dan pastinya bikin betah tinggal di bumi!  Selain itu, kita juga bisa menghemat uang dan nggak perlu kuatir kehabisan energi.  So, kapan kita mulai beralih ke energi hijau?\n', 'uploads/WhatsApp Image 2024-05-08 at 00.55.02.jpeg', '2024-05-07 17:16:39', 1, 'rejected', 'a', NULL),
(61, 'Mahasiswa KKN UNS Kenalkan Sustainable Energy ke Siswa SD dan Masyarakat Desa Kepyar, Wonogiri', 'Mahasiswa KKN UNS Kenalkan Sustainable Energy ke Siswa SD dan Masyarakat Desa Kepyar, Wonogiri Mahasiswa KKN UNS Kenalkan Sustainable Energy ke Siswa SD dan Masyarakat Desa Kepyar, Wonogiri Mahasiswa KKN UNS Kenalkan Sustainable Energy ke Siswa SD dan Masyarakat Desa Kepyar, Wonogiri Mahasiswa KKN UNS Kenalkan Sustainable Energy ke Siswa SD dan Masyarakat Desa Kepyar, Wonogiri Mahasiswa KKN UNS Kenalkan Sustainable Energy ke Siswa SD dan Masyarakat Desa Kepyar, Wonogiri Mahasiswa KKN UNS Kenalkan Sustainable Energy ke Siswa SD dan Masyarakat Desa Kepyar, Wonogiri Mahasiswa KKN UNS Kenalkan Sustainable Energy ke Siswa SD dan Masyarakat Desa Kepyar, Wonogiri Mahasiswa KKN UNS Kenalkan Sustainable Energy ke Siswa SD dan Masyarakat Desa Kepyar, Wonogiri Mahasiswa KKN UNS Kenalkan Sustainable Energy ke Siswa SD dan Masyarakat Desa Kepyar, Wonogiri', 'uploads/BlogPageBody_Image_showing_energy_crisis_with_fossil_fuels_becoming_scarce_and_rising_CO2_emissions (2).png', '2024-05-08 03:10:31', 1, 'approved', '', NULL),
(96, 'Bye Bye Sampah, Hai Energi! Inovasi Keren Energi Biomassa', '<p>Bosan sama tagihan listrik yang bikin dompet tipis???? Pusing lihat tumpukan sampah yang makin menggunung???? Ada kabar baik nih!! Energi biomassa, sang jagoan baru yang bisa mengubah masalah sampah jadi solusi energi masa depan!</p><p><i><strong>Emang Energi Biomassa itu Apa Sih?</strong></i></p><p>Gampangnya, energi biomassa itu energi yang dihasilkan dari \"bakar-bakaran\" bahan organik. Bahan organiknya bisa macem-macem, misalnya dari sisa makanan di dapur kita, daun kering di kebun, ranting pohon bekas tebas, bahkan limbah pabrik yang udah nggak kepake. Hasil pembakarannya nggak langsung jadi listrik, tapi diubah dulu jadi uap yang muterin turbin, baru deh bisa nyalain lampu rumah kita keren, kan?</p><p><i><strong>Kenapa Energi Biomassa Keren?</strong></i></p><p>Banyak alasan kenapa energi biomassa ini jagoan masa depan. Pertama, dia <strong>ramah lingkungan</strong>. Nggak kayak bahan bakar fosil yang bikin emisi gas buang-buang, energi biomassa ini malah bantu ngurangin gas rumah kaca. Kedua, dia bisa jadi superhero buat <strong>ngatasin masalah sampah</strong>. Bayangin aja, tumpukan sampah yang biasanya bersarang di TPA bisa diubah jadi energi. Ketiga, energi biomassa ini bisa diproduksi <strong>secara lokal</strong>. Jadi, nggak perlu lagi tergantung impor energi dari negara lain. Terakhir, dia bisa <strong>ciptain lapangan kerja baru</strong> di bidang pertanian, kehutanan, dan manufaktur. Keren banget, kan?</p><p><strong>Inovasi Keren Energi Biomassa</strong></p><p>Teknologi energi biomassa ini nggak jalan di tempat lho! Para ilmuwan terus berinovasi biar energi biomassa ini makin efisien dan bisa dimanfaatin lebih luas. Nih, beberapa contoh inovasi kerennya:</p><ul><li><strong>Teknologi Gasifikasi</strong>: Bisa mengubah sampah jadi gas sintesis yang bisa dipakai buat listrik, bahan bakar, dan produk kimia lainnya. Keren, kan? Kayak sulap aja!</li><li><strong>Teknologi Pirolisis</strong>: Benerin aja bacanya, pi-ro-li-sis. Teknologi ini bisa mengubah sampah jadi arang, bio-oil, dan gas yang bisa dipakai buat macem-macem keperluan. Serba guna banget!</li><li><strong>Teknologi Fermentasi</strong>: Nah, kalo ini akrab di kuping kita. Mirip kayak bikin tape ketan. Teknologi ini bisa mengubah sampah jadi biofuel kayak ethanol dan biodiesel. Jadi, kendaraan kita bisa jalan pake energi dari sisa makanan kita!</li></ul><p><strong>Yuk, Dukung Energi Biomassa!</strong></p><p>Kita semua bisa jadi pahlawan energi lho! Caranya gampang:</p><ul><li>&nbsp;Misahin sampah organik kayak sisa makanan dan daun-daun kering dari sampah plastik dan lainnya. Biar nanti sampah organiknya bisa diolah jadi energi.</li><li>Dukung produk kayak biofuel, bahan bangunan, dan tekstil yang terbuat dari bahan biomassa. Dengan beli produk ini, kita secara nggak langsung ngedukung penggunaan energi biomassa.</li><li>Pohon adalah sumber biomassa yang penting. Tanam pohon di halaman rumah atau ikut gerakan penghijauan. Selain bikin udara seger, juga bisa jadi sumber energi masa depan.</li><li>Kalo ada kebijakan pemerintah yang mendukung pengembangan energi biomassa, kasih jempol! Supaya energi biomassa bisa berkembang pesat di Indonesia.</li></ul><p>Dengan dukung energi biomassa, kita bisa ciptain masa depan yang lebih hijau dan bebas dari ketergantungan energi. Yuk, mulai dari langkah kecil dan jadi bagian dari perubahan ini!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><br>&nbsp;</p>', 'uploads/WhatsApp Image 2024-05-09 at 14.08.13.jpeg', '2024-05-10 03:36:45', 1, 'approved', '', 'bye-bye-sampah-hai-energi-inovasi-keren-energi-biomassa\n'),
(97, ' Angin Bisa Jadi Listrik? Ini Cara Kerja Energi Terbarukan yang Unik!!!', '<p>Kalian pernah ngelihat kincir angin raksasa yang muter-muter di bukit atau pantai? Kincir angin itu bukan cuma pemanis pemandangan, gengs! &nbsp;Mereka jagoan yang bisa menghasilkan listrik, keren kan? &nbsp;Mungkin kamu mikir, \"Hah, angin kok bisa jadi listrik?\" &nbsp;Tenang, sekarang kita bongkar rahasia di balik energi terbarukan yang unik ini!</p><p>1. Angin Kencang, Baling-baling Ikutan Kencang!</p><p>Pertama, kincir angin punya baling-baling gede yang dirancang khusus. Baling-baling ini kayak sayap pesawat terbang yang didesain buat ngeluarin performa maksimal pas ngelawan angin. &nbsp;Semakin kenceng anginnya, semakin cepet putaran baling-balingnya. &nbsp;Bayangin kayak kamu lagi main layangan, layangannya bakal terbang tinggi kalau anginnya kenceng, kan?</p><p>2. Poros Baling-baling Terhubung ke Generator</p><p>Poros yang nempel di tengah baling-baling ini nyambung ke generator. Nah, generator ini alat canggih yang bisa ngubah energi gerak putaran baling-baling jadi energi mekanik. Gimana kalo kamu bayangin kamu lagi ngegowes sepeda statis? &nbsp;Energi gerak kamu itu diubah jadi energi mekanik yang bisa membuat roda berputar, kan? &nbsp;Nah, prinsipnya mirip kayak gitu!</p><p>3. Energi Mekanik Jadi Listrik!</p><p>Generator nggak berhenti cuma di energi mekanik aja. Generator ini punya kumparan magnet yang bisa ngubah energi mekanik tadi jadi energi listrik. Prosesnya agak rumit, tapi bayangin kayak kamu ngesetin tali dynamo di sepeda kamu. &nbsp;Gesekan tali itu sama magnet di dynamo bakal ngubah energi gerak kamu jadi energi listrik buat ngasih lampu sepeda kamu nyala. &nbsp;Keren, kan?</p><p>4. Energi Listrik Dialirkan ke Jaringan Listrik!</p><p>Listrik yang dihasilkan generator ini nggak cuma dipakai kincir angin doang. &nbsp;Listrik dialirin ke gardu listrik lewat kabel bawah tanah atau kabel udara. &nbsp;Dari gardu listrik, baru deh listrik didistribusikan ke rumah, sekolah, pabrik, dan tempat-tempat lain. &nbsp;Jadi, nggak cuma kincir angin aja yang ngerasain manfaat angin kenceng, tapi juga hp kamu di rumah!</p><p>Kenapa Energi Angin itu Keren Abis????</p><p>* Ramah Lingkungan: Tidak seperti ngebakar bensin yang ngeluarin gas rumah kaca dan bikin polusi udara, energi angin bebas emisi! &nbsp;Bumi jadi sehat dan nggak gampang panas.<br>* Sumber Tak Terbatas: Angin tuh kayak temen yang selalu ada, bisa diandalin. &nbsp;Kita nggak perlu takut kehabisan angin kayak kita takut kehabisan bensin.&nbsp;<br>* Hemat Budget: Lama-lama, energi angin lebih murah dibanding listrik biasa. &nbsp;Bayangin, kamu nggak perlu beli bensin lagi buat ngasih listrik ke rumah kamu!<br>* Fleksibel Banget: Kincir angin bisa dipasang di darat atau di laut, bebas deh! &nbsp;Asal ada angin kenceng, energi bisa dihasilkan.</p><p>Yuk, Dukung Energi Terbarukan!</p><p>Dengan pake energi terbarukan kayak angin, kita bisa bikin masa depan yang lebih sehat, keren, dan pastinya bikin betah tinggal di bumi! &nbsp;Selain itu, kita juga bisa menghemat uang dan nggak perlu kuatir kehabisan energi. &nbsp;So, kapan kita mulai beralih ke energi hijau?<br>&nbsp;</p>', 'uploads/WhatsApp Image 2024-05-08 at 00.55.02.jpeg', '2024-05-10 03:37:34', 1, 'approved', '', 'angin-bisa-jadi-listrik-ini-cara-kerja-energi-terbarukan-yang-unik\n'),
(98, 'Energi Hijau Masa Depan! Membongkar Mitos & Fakta Energi Terbarukan!!!', '<p>Pernah kah kalian dengar tentang energi terbarukan? Kalo belum, yuk simak blog ini! &nbsp;Di era modern ini, bumi kita mulai ngos-ngosan nih. Polusi makin parah, perubahan iklim makin ngeri. Salah satu solusinya? Beralih ke energi hijau alias energi terbarukan! &nbsp;Tapi kenapa ya, banyak banget mitos yang beredar tentang energi terbarukan. Katanya sih mahal, gak efisien, gak bisa ngecover kebutuhan energi, ribet, dan lain sebagainya. Bener gak sih? &nbsp;Yuk, kita bongkar mitos-mitos itu bareng-bareng! &nbsp;Mitos ke-1: Energi Terbarukan Mahal dan Gak Efisien! &nbsp;Faktanya: Dulu sih emang iya, teknologinya masih mahal. Tapi sekarang udah jauh lebih murah! Efisiensi energi terbarukan juga terus meningkat, contohnya tenaga surya dan angin yang sekarang udah bisa menghasilkan energi yang cukup besar. &nbsp;Mitos ke-2: Gak Bisa Penuhi Kebutuhan Energi Global &nbsp;Faktanya: Potensi energi terbarukan di bumi tuh gede banget, jauh lebih besar dari kebutuhan energi global. Contohnya, energi matahari yang mencapai bumi dalam satu jam aja cukup buat memenuhi kebutuhan energi seluruh dunia selama setahun! &nbsp;Mitos ke-3: Energi Terbarukan tuh Cuman Cocok Buat Negara Maju &nbsp;Faktanya: Salah banget! Negara berkembang kayak Indonesia tuh punya potensi besar banget buat manfaatin energi terbarukan. Iklim tropis yang cerah dan sumber daya alam yang melimpah bikin Indonesia cocok banget buat ngembangin energi surya, panas bumi, dan energi angin. &nbsp;Mitos ke- 4: Energi Terbarukan itu Gak Stabil dan Gak Bisa Diandalkan &nbsp;Faktanya: Teknologi penyimpanan energi kayak baterai terus berkembang pesat, jadi energi terbarukan bisa disimpan dan dipake pas dibutuhkan. Kombinasi berbagai sumber energi terbarukan juga bisa bantu atasi intermittency dan memastikan pasokan energi yang stabil. &nbsp;Mitos ke-5: Gak Ramah Lingkungan &nbsp;Faktanya: Energi terbarukan kayak tenaga surya, angin, dan air gak menghasilkan emisi gas rumah kaca yang bikin perubahan iklim. Gak cuma itu, energi terbarukan juga gak menghasilkan limbah berbahaya kayak energi fosil. &nbsp;Jadi Kesimpulan nya adalah: &nbsp;Energi terbarukan bukan cuma solusi masa depan, tapi juga solusi masa kini! &nbsp;Teknologi terus berkembang, biayanya makin murah, dan kesadaran akan kelestarian lingkungan makin tinggi. Yuk, kita sama-sama beralih ke energi hijau dan ciptakan masa depan yang lebih cerah dan berkelanjutan!</p>', 'uploads/WhatsApp Image 2024-05-08 at 00.26.28.jpeg', '2024-05-10 03:41:54', 1, 'approved', '', 'energi-hijau-masa-depan-membongkar-mitos-fakta-energi-terbarukan\n'),
(99, 'Each year the stakes grow higher in the fight to s...', '<p>Each year the stakes grow higher in the fight to save the environment and combat global warming. Now more than ever, we’re aware of the damaging effects that our current dependence on fossil fuels holds for our collective futures. One of the key solutions? Sustainable energy.</p><p>Fossil fuels (e.g. coal, natural gas and oil) are not only harmful to the planet when burned daily for energy, but they’re also unsustainable as finite resources. Sustainability refers to the concept that all people can meet their basic needs infinitely, without compromising future generations. Sustainability in terms of energy embraces the same principles.</p><p>One day the world will run out of fossil fuels. Read on to discover how sustainable energy matters and its significance when it comes to the future of our planet.</p><p>What is sustainable energy?<br>Sustainable energy includes any energy source that cannot be depleted and can remain viable forever. It does not need to be renewed or replenished; sustainable energy meets our demand for energy without any risk of going bad or running out. This is why sustainable energy is the answer to our energy needs.</p><p>Furthermore, sustainable energy doesn’t harm the environment (or at most, there is a minimal risk), increase climate change or cost a heavy price. Although there is a cost associated with creating and building ways to capture sustainable energy, the energy sources themselves are typically free.</p><p>Examples of sustainable energy sources include wind, solar and water (hydropower). All of which can be considered inexhaustible and widely available to almost everyone. Geothermal energy can also be included as a sustainable alternative energy source. Geothermal energy creates usable energy from the planet’s internal energy sources, such as geysers.</p><p>Sustainable energy systems are dependent upon engineers to further progress. For an in-depth introduction to sustainable energy, explore Toolseeram Ramjeawon’s “Introduction to Sustainability for Engineers.” This book provides students with a framework for how to put sustainability into practice. It also highlights the design process and offers a variety of case studies to comprehensively cover sustainable energy.</p><p>What is the difference between sustainable and renewable energy?<br>People often use the terms “sustainable” and “renewable” interchangeably. However, there is a difference between the two: the possibility of replenishment.</p><p>Sustainable energy, as highlighted above, is theoretically inexhaustible. It cannot be depleted because sustainable energy sources don’t need to be replenished. For example, think of the sun or wind. Neither resource needs to be created or replaced.</p><p>On the other hand, renewable energy is theoretically exhaustible — it uses resources from the earth that can naturally be replenished, such as crops and biomatter. A renewable energy source like bioenergy uses biological masses (e.g. agricultural byproducts like straw and manure) to create energy. Another example of bioenergy is ethanol, which is made from sugarcane and corn. Since these crops can be planted and farmed to generate more energy, it’s a type of renewable energy. For more information on renewable energy systems, take a look at Vladimir Strezov and Hossain Md. Anawar’s “Renewable Energy Systems from Biomass: Efficiency, Innovation and Sustainability,” which explores the ties between bio-related renewable energy systems and overall sustainability:</p><p>Image showing energy crisis with fossil fuels becoming scarce and rising CO2 emissions. New renewable energy sources depicted.</p><p>Another helpful resource is Ram K. Gupta and Tuan Anh Nguyen’s “Energy from Waste: Production and Storage,” which considers how waste from various sources can be used in energy production and storage applications. It similarly discusses the connections between renewable energy systems and long-term sustainability.</p><p>Different types of renewable energy are just as important in the search for clean energy options because they don’t pollute the atmosphere, increase climate change or cause more damage to the environment.</p><p>What are the benefits of sustainable energy?<br>There is a broad range of benefits to transitioning to sustainable energy. Below we’ll list the top ways sustainable energy can positively impact our communities and planet:</p><p>Icon image of a heart beat line leading to a heart - to represent health and the importance of healthImproves Public Health<br>The burning of fossil fuels in coal and natural gas plants is directly tied with many serious public health issues, such as neurological damage, cancer, heart attacks, breathing problems and premature death. When fossil fuels are burned for energy, they release air and water pollution that negatively affect surrounding communities and environments.</p><p>However, all of these associated risks can be eliminated by switching to sustainable energy. Sustainable energy sources typically emit no air or water pollutants that can harm public health. They also don’t make a negative impact or strain on local water resources. Meanwhile, coal mining, natural gas drilling and thermal power plants all compete with local agriculture, drinking water and other important community water needs for resources.</p><p>Icon image of a person running up an arrow with a briefcase - to represent work and sit by the copy about creating local jobsCreates Local Jobs&nbsp;<br>Sustainable energy can also help fuel your local communities. Since most facilities and sustainable energy infrastructure must be built locally or in the same county, making the switch helps create jobs and improve the economy. Instead of spending more money importing energy from fossil fuel companies, that money is spent on materials and workmanship to maintain sustainable energy facilities.<br>&nbsp;</p><p>Icon image of a foot with CO2 written on it - to represent carbon footprint and sit by the copy about decreasing your carbon footprintDecreases Your Carbon Footprint&nbsp;<br>We’re all doing our best to reduce our negative impact on the environment, but there is only so much each person can do. Sustainable energy, such as wind and solar energy, creates zero carbon emissions that can harm the atmosphere and contribute to global warming. It offsets the need for fossil fuels, which are actively increasing climate change and polluting our earth.</p><p>Simply switching your own home’s energy source can help cut the environmental impact you and your family have on the planet — and eliminate your dependence on fossil fuels.</p><p>Icon image of an energy coin falling into a piggy bank - to represent energy cost and sit by the copy about the long term cost of sustainable energy being more affordable Long-term Cost is More Affordable&nbsp;<br>Sustainable energy can make a huge long-term difference to the electricity and energy costs of our homes and businesses — no matter where you are. Not only are they easily available for little to no cost, but they’re much more cost-effective than traditional energy resources, such as power plants.</p><p><br>Making the financial leap to wind, solar or any other sustainable energy source may seem daunting at first because of installation costs, but the long-term investment pays off in just a few years. In fact, sustainable energy costs decrease each and every year. Depending on your country or state, you may even get tax reductions for choosing sustainable energy. Ultimately, you could end up saving exponentially just by making the switch to a sustainable energy system like solar panels.</p><p>Icon image of a padlock with an energy symbol on it - to represent energy security and sit by the copy about sustainable energy being the most reliable form of energy, thus providing security</p><p>Energy Security&nbsp;<br>Sustainable energy is by definition the most reliable form of energy. It will never deplete and can remove our reliance on imported fossil fuels, which are growing more expensive and less accessible. Sustainable energy also helps to conserve the planet’s natural resources and reduce the pollution associated with unsustainable energy.</p><p>Why is sustainable energy important for our future?<br>When we consider sustainable energy and our future, it’s essential to also understand what the current energy crisis is doing to our planet right now.</p><p>Due to human activity, the earth has grown 1.5 degrees hotter since the industrial revolution — a staggering amount in such a short period of time compared to pre-industrial revolution times. Many factors have contributed to this increase, but a major cause is our burning of fossil fuels for energy. The most prevalent greenhouse gas is carbon dioxide (CO2), which has triggered immense global warming.</p><p>Although carbon is an essential element within the earth’s ecosystem, there needs to be a sustainable balance — which is not the current situation. Carbon particles have become trapped in the earth’s atmosphere, between the surface and ozone layer. This is insulating our planet and warming it up, which is causing catastrophic effects: glaciers are melting, sea levels are rising and extreme weather events (e.g. hurricanes, heatwaves and floods) are escalating.</p><p>Beyond that, finite energy source facilities are polluting the air, water and soil increasingly every day. Besides destroying our natural environments, it’s causing undue harm to the health of people globally.</p><p>Although humans have done irreversible damage to the environment, there’s still hope in how we maintain and mitigate repercussions for future generations. The solution lies in how we stop flooding our atmosphere with carbon dioxide and reduce our emissions.</p><p>Remember, sustainable energy produces little to no global warming emissions. By choosing sustainable energy resources and committing to clean energy, humans can effectively slow down the acceleration of climate change.</p><p>To learn more about the chemistry behind sustainable energy, we have two books that can help you get started. Nancy E. Carpenter’s “Chemistry of Sustainable Energy” is a great resource for students who want to understand the fundamental principles of chemistry that tie into long-term energy solutions, including wind power, fuel cells, solar photovoltaics, biomass conversion processes and next-generation nuclear power.</p><p>For a university-level environmental chemistry approach integrated with toxicological chemistry, there is Stanley E. Manahan’s “Fundamentals of Environmental and Toxicological Chemistry: Sustainable Science.” This best-seller focuses on the relationship between sustainability and green chemistry, and how they impact the five environmental spheres (hydrosphere, atmosphere, geosphere, biosphere and anthroposphere).</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', 'uploads/taking-beautiful-photos-of-nature-2 (1).png', '2024-05-10 03:42:34', 1, 'approved', '', 'each-year-the-stakes-grow-higher-in-the-fight-to-s\n'),
